social_posts.post_text:
You all know how much I love talking about feeding tweens and teens: it's just as hard as feeding toddlers but no one really talks about it! Well, I had a great conversation on the topic with @vanessakrollbennett and Dr. @caranatterson of @thepubertypodcast . If you're #feedingteens this is a must-listen. Link in bio!⁣ - @staciebillis 
⁣
⁣
⁣

The winter holiday season is one of my favorite times of year. I for sure get tired and crabby, but not lonely. And there's always fun too. I feel so, so lucky about that. It always goes too fast, but I'm starting to accept that it always feels that way, even when it's also going too slow. Here's hoping that my 2023 is restful *and* exciting, my favorite combination, and that yours is whatever you want and need it to be too. Love you all 💖

Best view of 2022, hands down, trees be damned!!! In 2022, we traveled to Colombia, Mallorca, The Netherlands, and Paris. And y'all know that our wanderlust has led us to many places around the world, from Turkey to Machu Picchu, but after spending Bastille Day at the Eiffel Tower, my 13yo declared that it was one of the coolest things we've EVER done across any of our travels. 🇫🇷🗼🎇⁣
⁣
We already have our two big trips for 2023 planned. Big ones! Bucket list stuff as we approach our older son's second half of high school (gotta keep spring break 2024 free for college visits 😳😭). Any guesses of where we're going?! 😎👇🏻⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣

Day one, CDMX, in which I end up cooking street tacos. Not nearly as good as my teacher's, but you know I'm a sucker for at least trying. (I can't help myself!)⁣
⁣
✨ NYX ↔️ CDMX⁣
✨ Shower, rest and snack time (aka best ever room service) at @fourseasons CDMX⁣
✨ A pre dinner shot of @claseazulofficial with some crunchy, salty crickets.⁣
✨ A FANTASTIC Tacos at Night tour with my favorite @mexico_underground_tours led by the awesome @gab0176_mx (keep playing ball!! ⛹🏽‍♂️⁣
⁣
So. Much. Delicious. Food. I love you Mexico! 🇲🇽💚🤍❤️🤤⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
#cdmx❤️ #cdmxlife #cdmxfood #willtravelforfood #mexicocityfood

Day two #CDMX⁣
⁣
✨ sleep in & straight to a SUBLIME lunch at @exp_maiz - an homage to masa, no menu, no reservations, cooking on a wood-fired comal and in clay pots, everything more delicious than the next. 😭❤️⁣
✨ getting those steps in (SO many steps!)⁣
✨ evening drinks at @handshake_bar (recently named one of the top 50 bars in the 🌎). A tiny tini aperitif followed by a butter mushroom old fashioned, a cocktail inspired by Thai flavors (hi, basil oil!), and more!⁣
✨ we didn't think we'd be hungry after our lunch, but post-cocktail late night tacos at @taqueriaorinoco called 🤷🏻‍♀️⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
#mexicocityfood #cdmxfood #willtravelforfood #cdmx🇲🇽 #mexicocitylife #foodtravels #foodtraveller #mexicancuisine #bestrestaurants #bestbars
Someone tell the kids: we're reserving the right to do nothing tomorrow, thanks. ✈️😴🛌 #traveldays #travellingcouple #momswhotravel

Day 3 #CDMX ⁣
⁣
We got a late start on this day and, honestly, I felt a little crabby about it. There was a lot I wanted to pack into the day and was irritated at the thought of not fitting it all in. But @mikelebowitz, who is a far more relaxed about such things, reminded me that seeing everything on my list wasn't nearly as important as enjoying -- and surrendering to -- what the world shows us. And then, just like that, the day served us exactly what we needed most. ⁣
⁣
We even ignored tickets that we had to the Ballet Folklorico (which I WILL see next time - lol) because we got caught up meeting people and having great conversation. It was a magical day and a great reminder for me about travel and, fiiiiinnnnneeee, life too. 😜⁣
⁣
✨Lunch at @contramar 👉🏻 there has apparently been an explosion of great seafood restaurant openings in the last couple of years. Someone recommended Mi Compa Chava and someone else Con Vista al Mar, but never  having gone to the old school standby, we decided to start at Contramar. Everything was delicious and the Tuna Tostada lives up to the hype (omg fried leeks!). Lunch was the move for this place. Can't wait to go back and try the others. ⁣
⁣
✨ We walked TONS, found so many great shops and saw so much art. Roma Norte was our favorite of the neighborhoods we got to explore (there are many others we didn't). Some highlights included meeting Miguel at @conceptracer, chatting with Emmanuel at @chicbyaccident (we'll fly in for a good party 😜), and discovering @originario.originario my new favorite store of all stores anywhere 😭⁣
⁣
✨ More cocktails! Did you know that CDMX has 3 bars on the list of 50 best bars in the world? @limantourmx did not disappoint. I leaned into "before dinner drink" vibes: my first cocktail was a sorbet made of gin, Lillet Blanc, grapefruit & pink peppercorn topped with Prosecco. Think my @ninjakitchen Creami can help me make this at home?! 🤞🏻⁣
⁣
✨ We finished the night with a three spot taco crawl: @patomanila for duck tacos, @carinito.tacos (love for fusion flavors!), and @elcalifa_mx (holy delicious beef tacos that I'm still thinking about).⁣
⁣

⁣

Prepped a bunch of stuff to make high protein and veggie packed lunches easier this week. I threw in some nacho prep, too, because Super Bowl Sunday!⁣
⁣
✨ Quinoa for lunch bowls and to toss into salads. 🔥HOT TIP: Sometimes, I'll throw just a little bit of cooked quinoa into the air fryer to have crunchies for my salad!⁣
✨ Quick pickled onions & shallots, Cornichon, capers, olives, are all key to adding flavor to bowls, salad, and toasts.⁣
✨ I broke down a rotisserie chicken and sautéed the chopped meat with onion, some pico de gallo, and chipotle in adobo sauce. Added a can of black beans. Great for toasts, wraps, burritos, and bowls.⁣
✨ I like layering different greens in my bowls and salads. Lately, I've been combining chopped romaine, pre-shredded brussels sprouts, and lightly dressed cabbage in varying combos for salads and bowls. Cabbage is also great on tacos and nachos!⁣
✨ Hard boiled eggs, duh⁣
✨ Ready-to-go cilantro for something herbaceous and bright to finish off nearly anything.⁣
✨ Beef sautéed with onion, garlic, and @traderjoes guajillo salsa that I found in my pantry. Going to add black beans and use these for nachos tonight.⁣
✨ I KNOW. And the lighting in my kitchen doesn't help, but… Dijon and rosemary marinade make these chicken breasts tasty to top salads and build sandwiches. (It's great on sourdough with some pesto, sun-dried tomatoes, thinly sliced red onion, and melted mozzarella!)⁣
✨ Chia seed pudding, which I either eat for breakfast or combine with berries and #coolwhip  for my latest favorite dessert! 🤣⁣
⁣
⁣

‼️👉🏻 Keep better track of leftovers, save money. Seriously! The biggest waste of your grocery budget is food that goes to waste. The key to making sure you make good use of your leftovers is labeling them properly. We used to recommend sticking masking tape onto Tupperware and then writing on that, but who keeps masking tape in their kitchen?! This trick has made it so much easier!⁣

On our way from Kyoto and Osaka to Kanazawa, we spent a night in the countryside at an onsen, a traditional inn at a hot spring. There was a traditional public bath at our onsen, but obviously no cameras allowed (you must go into the baths nude). We were lucky enough to have a private bath in our room too. The boys were relieved to have their own bath, too, but each went in alone because teenage modesty. 😝 They also said that it was too hot to really enjoy. I disagree! Especially since the air had a just-right rainy chill! It was fabulous, and seriously... my skin was bizarrely soft afterwards! ⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
#triptojapan #familytravels #havekidswilltravel #showthemtheworld #familytrips #travelwithkids #travelwithteens #japaneseonsen #onsen♨️ #japanwithkids

2 days in Kanazawa, Japan: Katsu... served on a special plate rack (GENIUS!), nearing peak 🍒🌸 (I might have to give cherry blossoms an entire carousel, just sayin 🤷🏻‍♀️), tree support (because even plants have souls and deserve support to thrive; we saw tree supports everywhere!), delicious black sesame latte (@meghan_splawn !!!), gold leaf ice cream (Kanazawa is historically the arts and crafts center of Japan and gold leaf is made there), our now infamous sushi dinner... and the McDonald's the boys ate afterwards (with a side of Uno), more pictures-can't-do-them-justice blossoms, and being silly.⁣
⁣

What I ate in March, 2023. There are more Japan highlights coming, but I included just a few of my absolute favorite meals in Japan at the very end. ⁣
⁣
(1) If you listen to @didntijustfeedyou , you know that I'm obsessed with XCJ (recently rebranded to MìLà @eat.mila) frozen dumplings, and now they offer frozen noodles! I talk about them in tomorrow's upcoming ep of DIJFY, so you can learn more there. In the meantime, everyone in my family has requested a constant supply of their Sichuan Dan Dan Noodles that are easy enough for the kids to make for themselves.⁣
⁣
(2) Remember that time I tried my favorite childhood snacks for the first time in 30 years for a bonus episode of @didntijustfeedyou ? You can hear what I thought with a @applepodcasts subscription to DIJFY.⁣
⁣
(3) My every post-workout treat: a hot Ginger Turmeric Matcha Latte with almond milk from @chachamatcha⁣
⁣
(4) My new fave order at @gongcha.official : brown sugar milk tea with boba and a creme brulee top, regular ice and 30% sugar ⁣
⁣
(5) Pineberries! I found these in Manhattan Chinatown. They're a hybrid plant that's white with red seeds and said the taste of pineapple. Ours were just super tart. Maybe they weren't ripe enough? 🤷🏻‍♀️⁣
⁣
(6) I showed you this Okonomiyaki in my Osaka roundup, but it had all the toppings and you couldn't see the best part: the melty cheese. ⁣
⁣
(7) Tan Tan Udon: we're getting into my top Japan eats. ⁣
⁣
(8) 7-11 Pancakes with Maple Syrup & Margarine. @7eleven USA: what needs to happen to make these avail here?!?!⁣
⁣
(9) All the ramen: Holy shit this was good. We ordered a bunch of options made with different kinds of broth - thick, thin, with miso, without - and different toppings, each better than the last.⁣
⁣
(10) If you followed my trip to Japan in Stories, you know that we (well, the kids) had some major sushi highs *AND* lows. But our last night in Japan was spent at the restaurant of third generation sushi chef @yoshi_matsunozushi . Yoshi is way too cool and has done way more amazing things than I can list here — and our dinner with him was sublime. Every piece a sushi high.⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
#onmyplate #feedingmyfamily #feedingmyself #feedingkids #cookingforfamily

And perfect if you're celebrating a holiday this weekend that will leave you with a bunch of extra hard boiled eggs. ⁣

#stacieistoasted 👉🏻 had a good breakfast, went to the gym, had a protein water and then expected to have lunch in a timely way after that… But the day had other plans for me. By the time I came home I was absolutely STARVING. Low on groceries and put together an awesome toast using pretty much just pantry ingredients/things I tend to always have on hand. The salad is the only exception: just plain chopped cucumbers or even just red onion what it serve the same purpose just as well. And if you happened to have some herbs on hand – parsley, chives, basil - that would be good to you, but not absolutely necessary.⁣
 ⁣
I bet this would be good with a Friday as well as a boiled one, don't you agree?? 🍳🥚💕⁣

I set out to make a toast, but I had two pieces of bread… so a toasty sandwich? This one has a special vegan ingredient that I was curious to try. If you're an omnivore, it's not a substitute for the real deal, but this kinda of sandwich -- something that has big bold flavor that compliments the smokiness of the special ingredient -- is the perfect way to use it up. This was honestly delicious! (But don't skip that @traderjoes Calabrian chili or some other spicy/salty spread!) #stacieistoasted #groceryfinds #easylunchideas

A run down of our eats while traveling South Africa and Zimbabwe. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1. Every meal we enjoyed in SA and ZI had an abundance of veggies and salads — this was one of my faves: clementines, dates, and toasted cashews.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
2. Bobotie! Considered by many the national dish of South Africa, it's curried minced meat (usually beef) baked with an egg on top. The ultimate comfort food. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
3. A morning porridge.⁣
⁣
4. One of my boma dinner plates! A boma dinner is an outdoor, candlelit feast. Lots of grilled meats, plus beef stew and lots of veggies, from grilled squash to creamed spinach and roasted sweet potatoes. There was also always pap, a stick-to-your-ribs staple in this part of Africa made with white cornmeal (not unlike grits or polenta) served with chakalaka, an onion and pepper gravy. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
5. Snacks always included biltong made of all different kinds of meats, from beef to cudu. ⁣
⁣⁣
6. It's winter time in SA and ZI and I fell for soup (you heard right @didntijustfeedyou listeners!). Thank you SA for the inspo!!! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
7. Safari days start with a very early morning bite and coffee. Then, on your game drive, you'll stop for tea and pastries. Then, back to the lodge for a proper brunch. Then there's lunch. And 3 o'clock tea before heading out on a 2nd game drive, during which you'll stop for an early evening cocktail and more snacks. OMG. Then, of course, dinner. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
8. Nothing beats brunch by the fire after a cold, early morning  game drive. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
9. This is the meal we cooked in our Cape Malay cooking class in a Bo-Kaap house, hosted by the loveliest host/cooking teacher. We made potato samoosas, chile bites (like hushpuppies made with 1/2 chickpea flour and 1/2 AP flour), chicken curry, and homemade roti. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
10. I could hardly decide which photo to rep all of the fantastic restaurants we visited in Johannesburg and Cape Town, both of which have amazing restaurants. I just went with this one from @the_red_room_cw because I loved the meal and it was on my birthday (shout out to turning 48!). We also had the pleasure of eating at @basaltjhb @thepotluckclubct @grubandvine @baodownrestaurant @postcardcafestellenbosch @chefswarehouseatthebailey
